cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.DC 

The paper discusses a novel architecture for enabling vehicular applications by bringing general-purpose computational and storage resources to the vehicle. It also presents an application development framework for vehicles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as the paper focuses on vehicular technologies and their connectivity. The paper also discusses privacy/security concerns, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). The proposed architecture involves programmable dongles, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
